00:24:52,624 --> 00:24:55,863
You shaved thousands off their majority.
You did splendidly.

253
00:24:55,898 --> 00:24:57,942
Not splendidly enough.

254
00:24:57,977 --> 00:25:01,896
Ah I see. Self pity.

255
00:25:03,242 --> 00:25:05,720
No one is saying you don’t need
a safe seat.

256
00:25:06,364 --> 00:25:08,454
You deserve a safe seat.

257
00:25:10,214 --> 00:25:12,524
But it does not come unless
you learn to play the game a little.

258
00:25:12,750 --> 00:25:13,771
What game?

259
00:25:13,973 --> 00:25:16,075
You are a grocer’s daughter-

260
00:25:16,257 --> 00:25:18,866
And proud of being.
- in their eyes.

261
00:25:21,045 --> 00:25:23,033
A single grocer’s daughter.

262
00:25:24,377 --> 00:25:27,792
But if you were to become the wife
of a moderately successful businessman-

263
00:25:27,827 --> 00:25:28,887
You’d get to parliament,

264
00:25:29,897 --> 00:25:31,903
and I’d get to be
the happiest man in...

265
00:25:33,267 --> 00:25:35,098
in wherever they select you.

266
00:25:49,753 --> 00:25:51,290
Margaret, will you marry me?

267
00:25:56,173 --> 00:25:56,973
Well?

268
00:26:02,157 --> 00:26:05,175
Yes. Yes!

269
00:26:08,034 --> 00:26:08,935
What?

270
00:26:09,246 --> 00:26:11,768
I love you so much but...

271
00:26:11,803 --> 00:26:14,770
I will never be one of those women Denis-

272
00:26:14,805 --> 00:26:18,666
who stays silent and pretty on the arm
of her husband.

273
00:26:19,223 --> 00:26:24,140
Or remote and alone in the kitchen
doing the washing up for that matter.

274
00:26:24,154 --> 00:26:25,871
We’ll get a help for that.
- No...

275
00:26:26,583 --> 00:26:30,510
one’s life must matter, Denis.

276
00:26:31,174 --> 00:26:34,977
Beyond the cooking and
the cleaning and the children,

277
00:26:35,012 --> 00:26:37,854
one’s life must mean more than that-

278
00:26:37,889 --> 00:26:42,060
I cannot die washing up a tea cup.

279
00:26:42,966 --> 00:26:45,294
I mean it Denis,

280
00:26:46,918 --> 00:26:48,780
say you understand.

281
00:26:49,631 --> 00:26:51,957
That’s why I want to marry you, my dear.

282
00:27:10,233 --> 00:27:11,558
Now eat.

283
00:28:16,368 --> 00:28:18,919
There they are, my little twins.

284
00:28:34,991 --> 00:28:37,919
Cornwall, wasn’t it?
Bloody hell...

285
00:28:40,676 --> 00:28:43,507
Look at ‘em, little imps.

286
00:28:47,583 --> 00:28:50,314
You never really got golf, did you?

287
00:28:52,960 --> 00:28:54,307
You look happy.

288
00:28:54,519 --> 00:28:58,875
Yes, I do, don’t I?
You’re drinking too much.

289
00:29:01,249 --> 00:29:02,400
Whatcha doing?

290
00:29:02,435 --> 00:29:04,246
Not like you. Looking back.

291
00:29:04,925 --> 00:29:08,373
Don’t want to dig around too deep,
M. Don’t know what you might find.

292
00:29:11,040 --> 00:29:13,321
You can rewind it, but you can’t
change it.

293
00:29:15,315 --> 00:29:17,966
They grow up so fast.

294
00:29:56,944 --> 00:29:58,839
Mr Eric Deakins,

295
00:29:58,874 --> 00:30:02,983
Labour...
13,437...

296
00:30:08,127 --> 00:30:13,966
Mr xxxx lib...
12,260

297
00:30:18,897 --> 00:30:20,704
Mrs Marg.. Thatcher

298
00:30:20,739 --> 00:30:25,334
con... 29,697

299
00:30:25,963 --> 00:30:31,188
xxx

300
00:30:31,993 --> 00:30:34,269
Mrs Marg.. Thatcher.

301
00:30:40,420 --> 00:30:45,710
xxx... Please.

