she’s also credited,
with her friend Ronald Reagan,

625
00:56:23,843 --> 00:56:27,006
with a decisive role in the ending
of the Cold War.

626
00:56:27,041 --> 00:56:29,496
Her supporters claim she
transformed the British...

627
00:56:29,531 --> 00:56:33,007
economy and reversed
the country’s post-war decline.

628
00:56:33,042 --> 00:56:36,119
Her detractors blame her
savage public spending...

629
00:56:36,154 --> 00:56:39,159
cuts and sweeping privatization of -

630
00:56:44,684 --> 00:56:48,254
I don’t recognize myself.

631
00:57:12,329 --> 00:57:14,728
Am I out of the doghouse yet?

632
00:57:18,805 --> 00:57:22,726
They’re unveiling that portrait...

633
00:57:22,761 --> 00:57:25,507
of me at Number 10
next month.

634
00:57:29,097 --> 00:57:31,506
The invitation’s on the mantelpiece.

635
00:57:32,334 --> 00:57:33,209
So...

636
00:57:34,230 --> 00:57:35,386
there’ll be Churchill,

637
00:57:35,421 --> 00:57:38,515
Lloyd George and me.

638
00:57:39,266 --> 00:57:40,951
Just the three of us.

639
00:57:43,420 --> 00:57:48,274
I said I didn’t want any big fuss
but they insisted.

640
00:57:49,224 --> 00:57:52,189
Lovely little article in The Telegraph.

641
00:57:54,068 --> 00:57:57,807
The Woman Who Changed
the Face of History.

642
00:58:03,671 --> 00:58:06,948
Less than two years ago,

643
00:58:06,983 --> 00:58:10,046
the Prime Minister quoted St. Francis...

644
00:58:12,568 --> 00:58:16,501
and talked about bringing faith,

645
00:58:16,536 --> 00:58:18,874
hope and harmony to this country.

646
00:58:21,912 --> 00:58:23,668
Denis?

647
00:58:35,748 --> 00:58:37,965
Can the Right Honourable Lady deny,

648
00:58:38,000 --> 00:58:40,612
that having brought about
the highest level...

649
00:58:40,647 --> 00:58:43,957
of unemployment since 1934-

650
00:58:45,772 --> 00:58:47,842
The biggest fall in total output...

651
00:58:47,880 --> 00:58:51,586
in steel and coal production
in one year since 1931.

652
00:58:53,052 --> 00:58:58,484
And the biggest collapse in
industrial production since 1921.

653
00:58:58,519 --> 00:59:00,360
Order, Order.

654
00:59:02,457 --> 00:59:07,749
Can she also accept that her
free market economics...

655
00:59:07,784 --> 00:59:11,279
designed to create a
growing middle class...

656
00:59:11,314 --> 00:59:16,387
ensures that the rich get richer
and the poor are irrelevant!

657
00:59:16,422 --> 00:59:19,074
Maggie Maggie Maggie! Out Out Out!
Maggie Maggie Maggie! Out Out Out!

658
00:59:22,851 --> 00:59:24,739
You’re supposed to be a mother!

659
00:59:24,774 --> 00:59:27,302
You’re not a mother,
you’re a monster!

660
00:59:29,067 --> 00:59:30,641
May we have a word,
Prime Minister?

661
00:59:30,676 --> 00:59:34,326
Yes, but in order to arrive
at the palace on time,

662
00:59:34,953 --> 00:59:37,617
Geoffrey and I are will be walking
out of that door in 15 minutes.

663
00:59:37,652 --> 00:59:39,595
As you can see.
- I know you’re running late Margaret...

664
00:59:39,630 --> 00:59:41,443
but we have to address this
situation in light...

665
00:59:41,478 --> 00:59:44,075
of tomorrow’s blistering
press coverage. Blistering!

666
00:59:44,104 --> 00:59:45,181
The knives are out.

667
00:59:45,216 --> 00:59:48,873
Your draft budget’s been leaked,
Geoffrey, they are baying for our blood!

668
00:59:48,908 --> 00:59:53,483
Michael we can’t possibly buckle
at the first sign of difficulty.

669
00:59:53,518 --> 00:59:55,976
No one is saying we have to buckle.
- But is this really the time to...

670
00:59:56,011 --> 00:59:58,714
make these spending cuts in the
middle of one of the deepest...

671
