Anchor butter is forty pence.

680
01:00:23,194 --> 01:00:27,095
Flora margarine, still the cheapest,
is thirty eight pence.

681
01:00:27,130 --> 01:00:30,198
I can assure you
I am not out of touch.

682
01:00:30,199 --> 01:00:31,953
“Grocer’s Daughter”

683
01:00:33,709 --> 01:00:37,118
What - did you say?

684
01:00:37,153 --> 01:00:38,253
Nothing. Prime Minister, Nothing.

685
01:00:38,288 --> 01:00:41,242
No, no, please.
Don’t try to hide you opinions.

686
01:00:41,277 --> 01:00:43,894
Goodness me, I’d much rather
you were open and...

687
01:00:43,929 --> 01:00:46,123
straight forward about them

688
01:00:46,158 --> 01:00:50,481
instead of continuously and
damagingly leaking them to the press.

689
01:00:55,367 --> 01:00:57,517
Well?
- Well,

690
01:00:58,038 --> 01:01:00,327
people can’t pay their mortgages.

691
01:01:00,362 --> 01:01:02,669
The manufacturing industry is
practically on its knees.

692
01:01:02,704 --> 01:01:06,169
Honest, hard-working, decent
people are losing their homes.

693
01:01:06,204 --> 01:01:07,426
It’s terribly shameful.

694
01:01:07,461 --> 01:01:10,015
The point is, Prime Minister, that
we must moderate the pace -

695
01:01:10,050 --> 01:01:12,238
- if we’re even to have a hope of
winning the next election-

696
01:01:12,273 --> 01:01:15,748
Quite right.
Ah. Worried about our careers, are we?

697
01:01:18,272 --> 01:01:21,300
Gentlemen, if we don’t cut
spending we will be bankrupt.

698
01:01:22,199 --> 01:01:24,290
Yes, the medicine is harsh...

699
01:01:24,325 --> 01:01:28,479
but the patient requires
it in order to live.

700
01:01:29,815 --> 01:01:34,981
Shall we withhold the medicine?
No! We are not wrong.

701
01:01:35,461 --> 01:01:39,893
We did not seek election and
win in order to manage...

702
01:01:39,928 --> 01:01:41,848
the decline of a great nation.

703
01:01:42,390 --> 01:01:44,973
The people of this country
chose us...

704
01:01:45,008 --> 01:01:48,383
because they believe we can
restore the health of

705
01:01:48,418 --> 01:01:51,232
the British economy and
we will do just that!

706
01:01:52,345 --> 01:01:54,397
Barring a failure of nerve.

707
01:01:56,219 --> 01:01:59,184
Anything else?
- Prime Minister.

708
01:01:59,219 --> 01:02:03,859
You saved the day
once again, Crawfie,

709
01:02:03,894 --> 01:02:05,667
you’re an angel.

710
01:02:07,238 --> 01:02:11,794
You can’t close down a discussion
because it’s not what you wish to hear.

711
01:02:11,829 --> 01:02:15,683
I don’t expect everyone just to
sit there and agree with me.

712
01:02:15,718 --> 01:02:18,866
But what kind of leader am I if I
don’t try to get my own way-

713
01:02:18,901 --> 01:02:21,005
to do what I know to be right.
- Yes.

714
01:02:21,948 --> 01:02:23,074
But Margaret,

715
01:02:25,137 --> 01:02:30,109
one must be careful of testing
one’s colleagues’ loyalty too far.

716
01:02:46,713 --> 01:02:49,249
We are now one split nation,

717
01:02:49,408 --> 01:02:53,506
with a huge gulf dividing
the employed from the unemployed.

718
01:02:54,523 --> 01:02:59,487
The Thatcher plan is to break
the Trade Union movement.

719
01:02:59,522 --> 01:03:03,337
There must be closures of
uneconomic coal mines,

720
01:03:03,372 --> 01:03:06,747
we seek only
an efficient industry.

721
01:03:06,782 --> 01:03:10,513
The miners are being starved back
to work, the need is desperate!

722
01:03:23,798 --> 01:03:26,454
There are those who would
say hold back,

723
01:03:26,489 --> 01:03:29,592
there are those who
would make us retreat -

724
01:03:29,627 --> 01:03:32,806
But we shall never
give in to them.

725
01:03:34,360 --> 01:03:37,298
We shall never waver,
not for a second,

726
01:03:37,749 --> 01:03:42,735
in our determination to see
this country prosper once again.

