01:04:03,982 --> 01:04:06,374
Seven horses also
died in the blasts.

732
01:04:06,409 --> 01:04:08,801
The IRA have claimed
responsibility.

733
01:04:20,323 --> 01:04:25,269
And now, it must be
business as usual.

734
01:04:35,382 --> 01:04:37,454
Come on love, get to bed.

735
01:04:38,237 --> 01:04:40,082
I don’t know why you do this
to yourself every year,

736
01:04:40,117 --> 01:04:43,370
it’s a speech at conference,
not the Magna Carta!

737
01:04:46,011 --> 01:04:50,740
Time to call it a day, darling.
It’s ten to three, for God’s sake.

738
01:04:50,775 --> 01:04:54,771
I know, I’m coming DT. Nearly
there -

739
01:05:06,800 --> 01:05:07,996
Denis!

740
01:05:12,251 --> 01:05:13,140
Denis-

741
01:05:18,313 --> 01:05:21,000
there you are.
Are you alright?

742
01:05:26,606 --> 01:05:28,048
My shoes!

743
01:05:37,425 --> 01:05:40,136
That’s when I thought I’d lost you.

744
01:05:50,651 --> 01:05:51,511
Mark?

745
01:05:53,694 --> 01:05:55,173
Hello darling.

746
01:05:57,356 --> 01:06:00,759
No, I’m fine.

747
01:06:00,794 --> 01:06:04,878
I’m very well, How is...

748
01:06:06,796 --> 01:06:07,812
Sarah?

749
01:06:09,155 --> 01:06:10,541
And the children..?

750
01:06:14,278 --> 01:06:15,443
Oh...

751
01:06:18,092 --> 01:06:19,407
You can’t.

752
01:06:20,787 --> 01:06:22,328
That’s a pity.

753
01:06:25,759 --> 01:06:28,478
I was hoping to see you.

754
01:06:30,588 --> 01:06:31,468
Yes...

755
01:06:31,503 --> 01:06:34,535
Oh... No That’s fine.
Really darling.

756
01:06:34,570 --> 01:06:36,217
That’s fine.

757
01:06:37,521 --> 01:06:40,791
Of course...
another time.

758
01:06:41,778 --> 01:06:43,207
Yes... Darling.

759
01:06:46,578 --> 01:06:48,610
Yes... Can’t wait... Lovely.

760
01:06:50,606 --> 01:06:51,586
Yes...

761
01:06:54,121 --> 01:06:55,864
xxx Mark?

762
01:07:22,190 --> 01:07:26,184
That was Mark. Not able to come.

763
01:07:26,219 --> 01:07:28,582
Boy’s always going AWOL.

764
01:07:28,617 --> 01:07:33,051
Well it costs him a great deal
to fly everyone up here.

765
01:07:33,086 --> 01:07:36,832
There you go, making excuses for
him. Now look where it’s got you.

766
01:07:38,258 --> 01:07:41,771
Did you know Yul Brynner was a
gypsy from Vladivostok?

767
01:07:41,806 --> 01:07:46,201
Yes. He moved to Paris
when he was fourteen.

768
01:07:46,236 --> 01:07:49,617
He played the King of Siam...

769
01:07:49,652 --> 01:07:55,651
4,625 times on the London
and Broadway stages.

770
01:07:56,563 --> 01:07:58,868
What are you doing?

771
01:07:58,903 --> 01:08:02,115
One likes to make an effort.
A snifter?

772
01:08:02,839 --> 01:08:05,273
You’re dead, Denis.

773
01:08:05,308 --> 01:08:10,637
Ah. Well, if I’m dead... who are
you talking to? Shall we dance?

774
01:08:51,416 --> 01:08:55,415
The Falkland islands, the British Colony
in the South Atlantic, has fallen.

775
01:08:55,450 --> 01:08:59,362
Argentina claims its marines went ashore
as a spearhead this morning...

776
01:08:59,397 --> 01:09:03,005
to capture key targets,
including the capital, Port Stanley.

777
01:09:03,039 --> 01:09:06,191
Gentlemen, the Argentinian Junta...

778
01:09:06,226 --> 01:09:08,807
which is a fascist gang...

779
01:09:08,842 --> 01:09:13,219
has invaded our sovereign territory.
This cannot be tolerated.

780
01:09:13,254 --> 01:09:17,499
May I make plain my
negotiating position.

781
01:09:17,534 --> 01:09:22,028
I will not negotiate with
criminals or thugs.

782
01:09:22,063 --> 01:09:27,531
The Falkland islands belong to
Britain, and I want them back.

783
01:09:28,470 --> 01:09:32,841
Gentlemen, I need you to tell me
today if that is possible.

784
01:09:32,876 --> 01:09:35,482
Possible... just, Prime Minister.

785
01:09:35,517 --> 01:09:38,588
We can have a Task Force ready
to sail in forty-eight hours.

786
01:09:38,623 --> 01:09:41,413
Forty-eight hours?
But...

787
01:09:41,448 --> 01:09:43,359
We have a very narrow
weather window.

788
01:09:43,393 --> 01:09:45,940
We can’t fight in winter down there.
Nobody can.

789
01:09:46,931 --> 01:09:50,887
If we are going,
we have to go now.

790
01:09:55,055 --> 01:09:59,046
Why were the islands left without
any naval protection?

791
01:09:59,081 --> 01:10:03,609
In the last round of Defence cuts
we judged the risk of invasion to be small.

792
01:10:03,845 --> 01:10:05,024
Did we?

793
01:10:05,055 --> 01:10:06,737
And if you remember, Prime Minister,

794
01:10:06,772 --> 01:10:11,589
you agreed that we should reduce the naval
presence in the area to an absolute minimum.

795
01:10:16,207 --> 01:10:19,588
Margaret, the cost
of sending 28,000 men...

796
01:10:19,623 --> 01:10:24,580
and a hundred ships twelve thousand miles,
almost to Argentina, will be absolutely crippling.

797
01:10:24,614 --> 01:10:28,173
I don’t think we should be worrying
about money at this point, Geoffrey.

798
01:10:28,208 --> 01:10:29,919
We can’t afford to go to war.

799
01:10:30,433 --> 01:10:32,279
We have to go now.

800
01:10:33,282 --> 01:10:34,475
now.

801
01:10:37,744 --> 01:10:43,148
The government has now decided
that a large task force will sail,

802
01:10:43,183 --> 01:10:47,294
as soon as all preparations
are complete.

803
01:10:49,846 --> 01:10:53,640
Prime Minister we do still have three
weeks before our ships reach the islands.

804
01:10:53,675 --> 01:10:57,602
All we’re saying is that we shouldn’t
give up on trying to find a diplomatic solution.

805
01:10:58,582 --> 01:11:01,818
The U.S. Secretary of State has
arrived, Prime Minister.

806
01:11:02,730 --> 01:11:06,810
So you are proposing to go to war
over these Islands.

807
01:11:07,282 --> 01:11:11,018
They’re thousands of miles away,
a handful of citizens,

808
01:11:11,053 --> 01:11:15,034
politically and economically insignificant,
if you’ll excuse me.

809
01:11:15,069 --> 01:11:18,638
Just like Hawaii, I imagine.

810
01:11:19,537 --> 01:11:20,839
I’m sorry?

811
01:11:20,874 --> 01:11:26,113
1941, when Japan attacked
Pearl Harbour.

812
01:11:26,148 --> 01:11:28,990
Did America go cap in hand...

813
01:11:29,025 --> 01:11:32,453
and ask Tojo for a peaceful
negotiation of terms?

814
01:11:32,487 --> 01:11:36,316
Did she turn her back
on her own citizens there...

815
01:11:36,351 --> 01:11:40,272
because the islands were thousands
of miles from mainland United States?

816
01:11:40,307 --> 01:11:44,227
No, no, no!

817
01:11:44,262 --> 01:11:49,056
We will stand on principle or
we shall not stand at all.

818
01:11:49,091 --> 01:11:53,657
But Margaret with all due respect
when one has been to war...

819
01:11:53,692 --> 01:11:55,425
With all due respect sir...

820
01:11:55,460 --> 01:12:00,303
I have done battle every
single day of my life...

821
01:12:00,337 --> 01:12:03,701
and many men have
underestimated me before.

822
01:12:03,737 --> 01:12:06,310
This lot seem bound
to do the same...

823
01:12:06,345 --> 01:12:10,184
but they will rue the day.

824
01:12:11,947 --> 01:12:14,165
Now, shall I be mother?

825
01:12:16,366 --> 01:12:19,193
Tea, Al, how do you take your tea?
Black or white?

826
01:12:32,234 --> 01:12:35,783
The Argentinian ship the General
Belgrano and her escorts are pursuing...

827
01:12:35,818 --> 01:12:39,461
course 273 degrees toward
the Argentinian mainland.

828
01:12:39,496 --> 01:12:42,290
We are tracking it with our
submarine HMS Conqueror.

829
01:12:42,323 --> 01:12:44,612
Is this ship a threat?

830
01:12:44,647 --> 01:12:47,815
Both of these ships are carrying
Exocet missiles, Prime Minister.

831
01:12:47,850 --> 01:12:49,820
Just yesterday...

832
01:12:49,855 --> 01:12:54,478
they launched, then aborted an
attack inside the exclusion zone.

833
01:12:54,513 --> 01:12:56,485
There is a risk they could
try it again.

834
01:12:56,520 --> 01:12:59,192
The Belgrano is sailing directly
away from the islands.

835
01:12:59,227 --> 01:13:01,315
Can it really be regarded
as a threat?

836
01:13:01,350 --> 01:13:03,464
She’s been changing course continually.

837
01:13:03,499 --> 01:13:07,934
There’s a strong possibility that they’re attempting
a pincer movement on our carrier group.

838
01:13:08,995 --> 01:13:11,434
I advise that we engage them:

839
01:13:12,161 --> 01:13:15,498
hit the Belgrano as a warning to the others.
Send them all back to port.

840
01:13:15,533 --> 01:13:19,188
It’ll play badly internationally.
We’ll be seen as aggressors.

841
01:13:19,223 --> 01:13:21,824
This will be an escalation, Prime Minister.

842
01:13:21,859 --> 01:13:24,871
If there is to be an escalation,
it’s better that we start it.

843
01:13:24,906 --> 01:13:27,807
It is steaming away, Prime Minister.

844
01:13:40,711 --> 01:13:42,069
Sink it.

845
01:13:58,143 --> 01:14:01,077
HMS Sheffield, a Type 42 destroyer,

846
01:14:01,112 --> 01:14:04,690
was attacked and hit late this
afternoon by an Argentine missile...

847
01:14:04,726 --> 01:14:09,309
it is seen as a retaliation for the sinking
of the General Belgrano,

848
01:14:09,344 --> 01:14:12,697
in which over 300 Argentinian
sailors died...

849
01:14:12,732 --> 01:14:16,227
xxx. Latest casualty figures
from the Sheffield.

850
01:14:18,278 --> 01:14:19,553
I must write to them.

851
01:14:20,789 --> 01:14:22,034
Prime Minister?

852
01:14:25,958 --> 01:14:27,148
The families.

853
01:14:30,730 --> 01:14:32,151
I must write to them...

854
01:14:32,152 --> 01:14:41,756
xxx

855
01:14:41,791 --> 01:14:42,826
Foreign Secretary...

856
01:14:43,804 --> 01:14:46,360
I’ve just been briefed by Admiral Fieldhouse.

857
01:14:46,395 --> 01:14:51,731
He told me bluntly that if the Argentinians
are prepared and willing to risk their aircraft,

858
01:14:51,766 --> 01:14:55,746
they have enough missiles
to cripple most of our fleet.

859
01:14:57,734 --> 01:15:00,332
President Reagan and President Bellaunde
of Peru have

860
01:15:00,367 --> 01:15:03,430
some new proposals
for the peace plan -

861
01:15:03,875 --> 01:15:05,071
The peace plan?

862
01:15:05,106 --> 01:15:08,993
There will be no appeasement.
This is a war.

863
01:15:09,028 --> 01:15:13,791
A war they started and
by God, we will finish it.

864
01:15:15,094 --> 01:15:18,065
I tell you what I’m going
to write...

865
01:15:18,100 --> 01:15:23,132
to every single one of these families,
these heartbroken families?

866
01:15:23,167 --> 01:15:28,159
I am going to tell them that no
British soldier will die in vain...

867
01:15:29,691 --> 01:15:31,191
for the Falklands.

868
01:15:31,226 --> 01:15:37,214
Lieutenant Colonel Jones.
Captain Wood. Captain Dench.

869
01:15:37,249 --> 01:15:41,328
I am the only Prime Minister
in the history of our country...

870
01:15:41,363 --> 01:15:45,570
who is also a mother with
a son of my own,

871
01:15:46,092 --> 01:15:50,356
I can imagine your agony,
and your grief.

872
01:15:52,285 --> 01:15:55,132
Prime Minister, we have secured
the beach head -

873
01:15:55,167 --> 01:15:58,731
The Argentinian troops are
demoralized and ill equipped...

874
01:15:58,766 --> 01:16:01,349
The paratroops have
taken Goose Green...

875
01:16:02,378 --> 01:16:07,240
Shortly after dark last night,
our forces xxx Port Stanley...

876
01:16:07,275 --> 01:16:13,194
xxx what the Commander in Chief
has called a brilliant surprise night attack.

877
01:16:20,848 --> 01:16:22,685
Thatcher, bed.

878
01:16:23,838 --> 01:16:28,694
From their new positions, our forces
can see large numbers of Argentine soldiers

879
01:16:28,729 --> 01:16:31,720
retreating and streaming back
into Port Stanley.

880
01:16:31,755 --> 01:16:35,806
Our forces are moving forward
to exploit their success.

881
01:16:56,542 --> 01:16:58,535
Well done, MARGARET.

882
01:16:59,593 --> 01:17:05,587
We congratulate the men and women
of the armed Forces for their skill,

883
01:17:05,622 --> 01:17:08,848
bravery and loyalty to this country.

884
01:17:09,718 --> 01:17:14,266
We were faced with an act of
unprovoked aggression...

885
01:17:14,301 --> 01:17:19,470
and we responded as we have
responded in times past:

886
01:17:19,505 --> 01:17:24,110
with unity, strength and courage,

887
01:17:24,588 --> 01:17:29,248
sure in the knowledge that
though much is sacrificed,

888
01:17:30,427 --> 01:17:35,206
in the end, right will prevail
over wrong.

889
01:17:37,998 --> 01:17:41,495
And I put it to the Honourable
Member opposite...

890
01:17:41,530 --> 01:17:44,990
that this is not a day
for him to carp...

891
01:17:45,025 --> 01:17:48,697
find fault, demand inquiries-

892
01:17:48,731 --> 01:17:51,962
they will happen I can assure
him of that...

893
01:17:52,451 --> 01:17:55,864
for we have nothing
to hide, no...

894
01:17:57,757 --> 01:18:01,232
this is a day to put difference aside,

895
01:18:02,100 --> 01:18:04,440
hold one’s head high...

896
01:18:05,263 --> 01:18:08,817
and take pride in being British.

897
01:18:32,514 --> 01:18:37,005
GOTCHA! Well that paid off old girl!
Your ratings soared!

898
01:18:37,040 --> 01:18:41,345
From the most hated Prime Minister
of all time to the nation’s darling...

899
01:18:41,380 --> 01:18:46,929
The world was at your feet,
and Britain was back in business!

900
01:19:14,590 --> 01:19:17,741
The Berlin Wall has fallen.
The gates have opened!

901
01:19:17,776 --> 01:19:21,098
The police are making no attempt to
stop people as they go through.

902
01:19:24,688 --> 01:19:28,251
I don’t agree...
I don’t agree in any measure!

903
01:19:28,286 --> 01:19:31,842
But Prime Minister the question of
the European single currency will come up.

904
01:19:31,877 --> 01:19:34,113
I don’t think the country
is ready for it yet.

905
01:19:34,148 --> 01:19:36,774
But we cannot bury our heads
in the sand...

906
01:19:36,809 --> 01:19:39,040
A lot of Conservative MP’s and
Ministers are saying -

907
01:19:39,075 --> 01:19:41,536
- that there must be a change in
that style of management.

908
01:19:41,571 --> 01:19:44,678
That Mrs Thatcher must listen more,
and on occasion, give in.

909
01:19:44,713 --> 01:19:46,189
The point is, Prime Minister,

910
01:19:46,224 --> 01:19:50,902
I don’t think we can sell the idea of
a tax that asks everyone to pay the same.

911
01:19:50,936 --> 01:19:55,006
Our policies may be unpopular, but
they are the right policies.

912
01:19:55,041 --> 01:19:58,607
Prime Minister I just don’t think
we can ask the poorest of the poor...

913
01:19:58,642 --> 01:20:01,495
to pay the same amount
of tax as a multi-millionaire.

914
01:20:01,529 --> 01:20:03,640
There it is again!
Why not?

915
01:20:04,175 --> 01:20:05,072
Because -

916
01:20:05,107 --> 01:20:10,043
Because people... on the whole...
think that the tax is manifestly unfair.

917
01:20:10,078 --> 01:20:12,426
Nonsense. Arrant nonsense.

918
01:20:12,461 --> 01:20:16,666
This is a simple proposition.
In order to live in this country,

919
01:20:16,701 --> 01:20:19,692
you must pay for the privilege-
something, anything!

920
01:20:19,727 --> 01:20:21,997
If you pay nothing,
you care nothing.

921
01:20:22,033 --> 01:20:24,922
What do you care where you
throw your rubbish?

922
01:20:24,957 --> 01:20:29,427
Your council estate is a mess,
your town, graffiti, what do you care?

923
01:20:29,462 --> 01:20:31,953
It's not your problem,
it's somebody else's problem-

924
01:20:31,988 --> 01:20:33,881
it's the government's problem!

925
01:20:35,516 --> 01:20:36,875
Your problem...

926
01:20:37,258 --> 01:20:38,540
Some of you,

927
01:20:39,567 --> 01:20:42,311
is that you haven't got
the courage for this fight.

928
01:20:42,862 --> 01:20:45,711
You haven’t had to fight
hard for anything.

929
01:20:45,746 --> 01:20:48,883
It's all been given to you-
and you feel guilty about it!

930
01:20:49,455 --> 01:20:53,769
Well, may I say, on behalf of all those
who have had to fight their way up,

931
01:20:53,804 --> 01:20:56,578
and who don't feel guilty about it...

932
01:20:57,468 --> 01:21:00,994
we resent those slackers
who take, take, take...

933
01:21:01,029 --> 01:21:03,301
and contribute nothing
to the community!

934
01:21:03,336 --> 01:21:06,653
And I see the same thing,
the same cowardice...

935
01:21:07,453 --> 01:21:09,463
in our fight within
the European Union.

936
01:21:09,498 --> 01:21:10,671
Cowardice.

937
01:21:10,706 --> 01:21:15,439
For the sovereignty of Britain
the integrity of the pound!

938
01:21:15,474 --> 01:21:20,731
Some of you want to make concessions.

939
01:21:21,794 --> 01:21:24,006
I hear some of you...

940
01:21:24,641 --> 01:21:28,570
agree with the latest
French proposals.

941
01:21:28,604 --> 01:21:31,268
Well, why don’t you get on
a boat to Calais?

942
01:21:31,303 --> 01:21:33,703
Yes, why don't you put on a beret,

943
01:21:33,739 --> 01:21:38,028
and pay 85% of your income
to the French government!

944
01:21:47,304 --> 01:21:48,103
Right.

945
01:21:49,423 --> 01:21:53,349
What can we realistically hope to achieve
by the end of session, Lord President?

946
01:21:53,384 --> 01:21:56,797
And why have we not made
more progress to date?

947
01:21:56,832 --> 01:22:00,388
What is that?
Is that the timetable?

948
01:22:00,423 --> 01:22:03,658
I haven't seen that.
May I see it?

949
01:22:03,693 --> 01:22:05,718
Here it is, Prime Minister. Of course.

950
01:22:12,748 --> 01:22:14,321
The wording is sloppy here...

951
01:22:17,842 --> 01:22:18,890
and here.

952
01:22:18,925 --> 01:22:21,610
If you say so.
- I do say so.

953
01:22:21,645 --> 01:22:23,583
It’s merely a first draft...

954
01:22:23,618 --> 01:22:29,580
This is ridiculous. There are
two “T’s” in “committee”!

955
01:22:29,615 --> 01:22:33,647
Two “T’s”.
This is shameful. Shameful!

956
01:22:37,448 --> 01:22:41,707
I can’t even rely on you for
a simple timetable!

957
01:22:41,742 --> 01:22:42,513
Are you unwell?

958
01:22:44,344 --> 01:22:47,826
Yes. You are unwell.

959
01:22:50,080 --> 01:22:52,380
Give me the pencil, give it to me!

960
01:22:57,948 --> 01:23:01,308
If this is the best you can do I
had better send you to hospital,

961
01:23:01,343 --> 01:23:04,830
and I shall do your job as well as
my own and everyone else’s.

962
01:23:04,865 --> 01:23:05,657
Gentlemen.

963
01:23:05,692 --> 01:23:09,436
As the Lord President has thosen
to come to cabinet unprepared...

964
01:23:11,236 --> 01:23:12,821
I have to close this meeting.

965
01:23:18,717 --> 01:23:19,599
Good morning!

966
01:24:12,194 --> 01:24:15,930
Can’t pay, won’t pay!

967
01:24:52,839 --> 01:24:53,707
Geoffrey-

968
01:24:54,560 --> 01:24:56,141
My letter of resignation.

969
01:25:00,197 --> 01:25:05,650
Our differences, I’m afraid,
cannot be reconciled.

970
01:25:17,649 --> 01:25:23,472
I have done what I believe to be right
for my party and my country.

971
01:25:24,622 --> 01:25:26,877
The time has come for
others to consider...

972
01:25:28,036 --> 01:25:32,361
their own response to the tragic
conflict of loyalties...

973
01:25:32,396 --> 01:25:34,743
with which I have myself wrestled
for perhaps too long.

974
01:25:34,778 --> 01:25:36,924
Geoffrey’s speech in the House of
Commons was devastating.

975
01:25:36,959 --> 01:25:38,466
xxx

976
01:25:38,501 --> 01:25:42,047
He was almost inviting someone to
challenge her for leadership of the party.

977
01:25:43,019 --> 01:25:44,238
She behaved appallingly.

978
01:25:44,273 --> 01:25:46,898
I wouldn’t have spoken to
my gamekeeper like that.

979
01:25:49,761 --> 01:25:51,455
I don’t think she can survive this.

980
01:25:52,369 --> 01:25:54,373
I’m here to announce my decision

981
01:25:54,840 --> 01:25:58,528
to put my name forward as leader
of the Conservative party.

982
01:25:59,850 --> 01:26:04,193
I have nothing but admiration for our
Prime Minister, Margaret Thatcher,

983
01:26:04,996 --> 01:26:05,962
but I believe...

984
01:26:06,894 --> 01:26:11,324
our party and our country
need a new leader.

985
01:26:12,270 --> 01:26:13,652
It’s extraordinary.

986
01:26:13,687 --> 01:26:17,069
I am the Prime Minister.
- The rules of the Conservative Party...

987
01:26:17,104 --> 01:26:21,523
make it possible for Conservative MP’s
to depose a sitting Prime Minister.

988
01:26:21,557 --> 01:26:22,335
Sweetie?

989
01:26:22,372 --> 01:26:23,847
xxx

990
01:26:23,882 --> 01:26:26,784
As Conservative MP’s gather
in Westminster to discus...

991
01:26:26,819 --> 01:26:29,879
who they will back in the leadership
contest, the Prime Minister said...

992
01:26:29,914 --> 01:26:33,332
she would not be diverted
from critical international affairs.

993
01:26:33,367 --> 01:26:37,770
Tonight in Paris Mrs Thatcher is
among thirty four world leaders

994
01:26:37,805 --> 01:26:41,554
who came together to celebrate
the end of the Cold War and herald...

995
01:26:41,589 --> 01:26:45,540
the start of a peaceful new age
of East/West cooperation.

996
01:26:45,964 --> 01:26:50,559
There’s a general feeling that Mrs Thatcher
is going to win on the first ballot.

997
01:26:50,594 --> 01:26:54,493
We’re going to put it to bed tomorrow night,
is how one of her campaign staff puts it.

998
01:26:56,322 --> 01:27:00,487
M, I really think you should come home
and defend yourself old girl.

999
01:27:00,522 --> 01:27:03,259
Heseltine is campaigning ferociously.

1000
01:27:03,294 --> 01:27:07,099
I do think my time is best spent seeing
an end to the Cold War...

1001
01:27:07,135 --> 01:27:10,808
don’t you? After all this time
they know what I stand for.

1002
01:27:12,493 --> 01:27:15,862
Will she, or will she not,
be in the job tomorrow?

1003
01:27:15,897 --> 01:27:20,232
Margaret, they can’t touch you.

1004
01:27:25,291 --> 01:27:29,320
Mrs Thatcher has failed to win
enough votes to secure an outright...

1005
01:27:29,355 --> 01:27:32,117
win in the leadership contest
and must now decide...

1006
01:27:32,152 --> 01:27:35,412
whether to put her name forward
for the second round.

1007
01:27:35,793 --> 01:27:40,143
As Mrs Thatcher leaves Paris for London
to make a last ditch attempt...

1008
01:27:40,178 --> 01:27:44,412
to pull together support for her
leadership, the ship may have sailed.

1009
01:27:47,149 --> 01:27:48,322
Treachery!

1010
01:27:49,093 --> 01:27:53,169
We will never win another election
led by that woman.

1011
01:27:53,204 --> 01:27:54,929
We need a leader who listens.

1012
01:27:54,964 --> 01:27:56,971
This isn’t about her,
it’s about the party.

1013
01:27:57,006 --> 01:27:58,927
One must know when to go.

1014
01:27:58,962 --> 01:28:01,359
The question is, how does
anyone put it to her?

1015
01:28:02,600 --> 01:28:06,506
If you were to stand, I of course
would vote for you Prime Minister-

1016
01:28:06,541 --> 01:28:10,088
of course would vote for you Prime
Minister, but I don’t think you can win.

1017
01:28:10,123 --> 01:28:12,831
The loyalty of my colleagues
cannot be counted upon.

1018
01:28:12,866 --> 01:28:14,199
It was the people who put me here -

1019
01:28:14,234 --> 01:28:17,542
The loyalty of my colleagues
cannot be counted upon.

1020
01:28:18,000 --> 01:28:21,643
- it’s up to them to tell
me when to go.

1021
01:28:21,678 --> 01:28:25,299
Margaret, you can’t let them
do this to you.

1022
01:28:26,969 --> 01:28:28,183
Please, boss.

1023
01:28:29,160 --> 01:28:33,453
They’ll destroy you.
Throw in the towel now, love.

1024
01:28:35,620 --> 01:28:38,526
Don’t let those bastards
see you humiliated.

1025
01:28:41,680 --> 01:28:46,145
You just won’t win, darling.
Not this time.

1026
01:28:49,327 --> 01:28:50,704
Oh Denis.

1027
01:28:54,465 --> 01:28:56,366
I am the Prime Minister.

1028
01:28:57,527 --> 01:28:59,950
Order! Order!

1029
01:29:00,060 --> 01:29:02,398
The Right Honourable gentleman is afraid!

1030
01:29:02,433 --> 01:29:06,030
This is a naked strategy of
closing some coal mines...

1031
01:29:06,065 --> 01:29:08,749
and then selling off.
- They believe in striking...

1032
01:29:08,784 --> 01:29:11,474
I believe in working!
- This is the woman who’s watched...

1033
01:29:11,509 --> 01:29:15,761
ten men on hunger strike starve themselves
to death and never flinched!

1034
01:29:15,796 --> 01:29:16,732
Despicable.

1035
01:29:17,563 --> 01:29:22,701
More homeowners, more
shareholders, more savings -

1036
01:29:22,702 --> 01:29:31,895
xxx

1037
01:29:31,930 --> 01:29:33,952
I offer my resignation...

1038
01:29:34,551 --> 01:29:37,846
after eleven and a half
extraordinary years -

1039
01:29:38,819 --> 01:29:42,863
proud to have left Britain in
a much better state...

1040
01:29:42,898 --> 01:29:44,446
than when we took office.

1041
01:29:54,264 --> 01:29:55,349
What’s this then?

1042
01:29:58,678 --> 01:29:59,812
A radio...

1043
01:30:01,525 --> 01:30:02,940
How useful.

1044
01:30:49,663 --> 01:30:51,005
Steady, MT.

1045
01:31:07,044 --> 01:31:09,620
The greatest Prime Minister
since Churchill...

1046
01:31:09,655 --> 01:31:12,816
deposed by a bunch
of spineless pygmies!

1047
01:31:12,851 --> 01:31:17,002
All those years of taking
the tough decisions...

1048
01:31:17,037 --> 01:31:19,226
does any of it matter now?

1049
01:31:19,260 --> 01:31:20,751
It’s all been turned to mush!

1050
01:31:20,786 --> 01:31:23,272
What?
- By these fools!

1051
01:31:23,307 --> 01:31:25,829
These lily-livered pinkos!

1052
01:31:25,864 --> 01:31:30,626
These inept placators.
- Very good! These vacillators.

1053
01:31:30,661 --> 01:31:34,562
Vacillators! Poll takers.
- Popularity seekers.

1054
01:31:34,597 --> 01:31:37,513
So busy taking the pulse of the public!

1055
01:31:37,548 --> 01:31:39,123
Weak.
Is weak.

1056
01:31:39,158 --> 01:31:42,241
Weak...
- All off them. Weak.

1057
01:31:42,277 --> 01:31:43,424
Men!

1058
01:31:46,655 --> 01:31:49,954
Don’t they know if you take
the tough decisions.

1059
01:31:51,839 --> 01:31:56,647
Yes, people will hate you today
but they’ll thank you for generations.

1060
01:31:56,682 --> 01:32:00,362
Or forget you entirely and chuck
you out with the rubbish!

1061
01:32:19,288 --> 01:32:23,153
All I wanted was to make a
difference in the world.

1062
01:32:23,188 --> 01:32:26,345
And you did, love, you did.

1063
01:32:33,622 --> 01:32:38,777
All I wanted was for my children
to grow up well and be happy...

1064
01:32:38,812 --> 01:32:41,629
happier than I was certainly.

1065
01:32:46,301 --> 01:32:49,079
xxx

1066
01:32:54,490 --> 01:32:55,442
Oh, yes.

1067
01:32:57,979 --> 01:33:00,435
And I wanted you to
be happy of course.

1068
01:33:00,470 --> 01:33:02,341
Were you happy, Denis?

1069
01:33:07,036 --> 01:33:08,638
Tell me the truth.

1070
01:34:30,901 --> 01:34:31,689
Denis?

1071
01:34:34,634 --> 01:34:35,602
Denis?

1072
01:34:39,630 --> 01:34:44,737
Here’s your bag.
You’re all packed, sorted.

1073
01:35:06,367 --> 01:35:10,156
Denis wait.
Where are your shoes?

1074
01:35:10,999 --> 01:35:14,149
No, you can’t go without shoes!

1075
01:35:16,632 --> 01:35:18,953
Not yet.
- Steady.

1076
01:35:20,780 --> 01:35:22,966
Yes.
Steady.

1077
01:35:23,297 --> 01:35:25,324
Steady the buffs.
- Steady the buffs.

1078
01:35:27,308 --> 01:35:31,382
No. Not yet. Denis.

1079
01:35:32,417 --> 01:35:33,510
Wait...

1080
01:35:34,294 --> 01:35:38,579
I don’t, I cant.
I don’t want you to go yet.

1081
01:35:39,377 --> 01:35:41,576
Denis. Please.

1082
01:35:42,634 --> 01:35:46,354
No, no. You are not.

1083
01:35:47,087 --> 01:35:50,609
I don’t want to be on my own.

1084
01:35:50,644 --> 01:35:55,658
You’re going to be fine on your own,
love. You always have been.

1085
01:35:59,997 --> 01:36:00,954
Denis!

1086
01:36:03,068 --> 01:36:05,602
xxx

1087
01:36:36,843 --> 01:36:37,745
Mummy-

1088
01:36:38,854 --> 01:36:41,851
My God, Mum.
Are you alright?

1089
01:36:41,886 --> 01:36:44,700
Yes.
- What are you doing.

1090
01:36:44,735 --> 01:36:46,428
Yes.

1091
01:36:46,463 --> 01:36:50,346
Mummy you should have called
for help, silly old sausage.

1092
01:36:51,372 --> 01:36:53,117
Have you not even been in
your bed properly?

1093
01:36:53,152 --> 01:36:56,668
You’ve done all this?
- Yes, all sorted.

1094
01:36:56,703 --> 01:37:00,975
Well don’t worry about all this.
June and I will crack on with it.

1095
01:37:01,010 --> 01:37:04,117
I was just going to get dressed.

1096
01:37:04,152 --> 01:37:07,760
Shall I call someone, see if anyone
can come over and do your hair?

1097
01:37:08,970 --> 01:37:12,261
Oh. No, you do it.

1098
01:37:35,931 --> 01:37:37,753
Oh, let me do that, Margaret.

1099
01:37:37,788 --> 01:37:40,635
No, dear, I’ll do it.

1100
01:37:41,500 --> 01:37:44,512
Carol said you might go to the
House of Lords today?

1101
01:37:44,547 --> 01:37:48,833
No no. I’m not going anywhere.

1102
01:40:19,817 --> 01:40:21,912
Noppes

